Changes to our privacy policy
Our company keeps its privacy policy under regular review and places updates on this web page.
California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018
If you are a California resident, California law may provide you with additional rights regarding our use of your personal information. To learn more about your California privacy rights, visit our CCPA Privacy Notice at
ctrlmovie.com/ccpapolicy.pdf
.
California’s “Shine the Light” law (Civil Code Section § 1798.83) permits users of our Service who are California residents to request certain information regarding our disclosure of personal information to third parties for their direct marketing purposes. To make such a request, please send us an e-mail to privacy@ctrlmovie.com
To the extent possible, users will receive equal service and price regardless of whether they exercise their privacy rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018. CtrlMovie does not sell the personal information of its users.
Rights of Japanese Users under the Act on the Protection of Personal Information (APPI)
If you are a resident of Japan, you are entitled to specific rights regarding the collection, use, and handling of your personal information under the Act on the Protection of Personal Information (APPI). These rights include, but are not limited to:
Right to Access: You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you, including the purposes for which it is being used and any third parties to whom it has been disclosed.
Right to Correction: You have the right to request corrections, additions, or deletions of your personal information if you believe it to be inaccurate, incomplete, or outdated.
Right to Suspend Usage or Deletion: Under certain circumstances, you may request that we suspend the use of, delete, or cease sharing your personal information if it has been handled improperly or if you withdraw your consent.
Right to Explanation: You have the right to request an explanation of the handling of your personal information, including the measures taken to ensure its security.
Right to Object to Certain Uses: You may object to the use of your personal information for purposes not previously disclosed or that exceed the scope of your consent, except where required by law.
To exercise these rights or for inquiries about our handling of personal information under APPI, please contact us via the following:
By email: privacy@ctrlmovie.com
CtrlMovie AG
Grenzstrasse 5a
6214 Schenkon
Switzerland
We will respond to your request within the timeframe stipulated by the Act, typically within one month, unless otherwise specified under applicable law.